{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 15, "line_start": 15, "page_hint": null, "section": "ABSTRACT", "text": "In December 1969, after more than 4 successful years, the nuclear operation of the MSRE was concluded and the plant was placed in standby."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 15, "line_start": 15, "page_hint": null, "section": "ABSTRACT", "text": "Work planned for early in FY-1971 includes removal of some core graphite; viewing inside the reactor vessel and inside the fuel-pump bowl; inspection of portions of the salt piping, the offgas charcoal bed, the coolant salt pump, and the control rods; and testing the coolant salt flowmeter."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 104, "line_start": 104, "page_hint": null, "section": "INTRODUCTION", "text": "To this end its design<sup>1</sup> incorporated essentially the same materials and many of the design features of proposed molten-salt power reactors."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 104, "line_start": 104, "page_hint": null, "section": "INTRODUCTION", "text": "Its primary purpose was accomplished as it was operated for more than 4 years at Oak Ridge National Laboratory."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 104, "line_start": 104, "page_hint": null, "section": "INTRODUCTION", "text": "Experience<sup>2</sup> with the MSRE was quite encouraging and a great deal of new information (particularly with regard to fission product behavior) was obtained."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 104, "line_start": 104, "page_hint": null, "section": "INTRODUCTION", "text": "In December 1969, the reactor was shut down because its original goals had been met and continued operation, although offering additional information, could not be justified in the very stringent budget situation."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 104, "line_start": 104, "page_hint": null, "section": "INTRODUCTION", "text": "In the interim the reactor was placed in a standby condition.<sup>3</sup>"}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 124, "line_start": 124, "page_hint": null, "section": "STEP5 IN DEFINING THE CAMPAIGN", "text": "In February 1969, the head of the MSRE Operations Department sent a request for suggestions for final operations and shutdown of the MSRE to group leaders in the MSRP."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 124, "line_start": 124, "page_hint": null, "section": "STEP5 IN DEFINING THE CAMPAIGN", "text": "Responses were consolidated to eliminate duplications and in October 1969, a tentative list of post-operation tasks was distributed with a request for comments."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 196, "line_start": 196, "page_hint": null, "section": "Investigation of Leak Near Freeze Valve FV-105", "text": "A leak appeared in the primary system on December 12, 1969 shortly after the scheduled end of nuclear operation."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 196, "line_start": 196, "page_hint": null, "section": "Investigation of Leak Near Freeze Valve FV-105", "text": "Correlation of changes in cell air activities with certain operations indicated that a small leak had developed in or near freeze valve FV-105 (leading to fuel drain tank FD-2) about two hours after the fuel was drained for the last time."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 208, "line_start": 208, "page_hint": null, "section": "Examination of Surfaces Inside the Fuel-Pump Bowl", "text": "A sample capsule was dropped into the pump bowl in August 1967 and another in March 1968."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 208, "line_start": 208, "page_hint": null, "section": "Examination of Surfaces Inside the Fuel-Pump Bowl", "text": "The steel cap of the first capsule was retrieved in May 1968."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 214, "line_start": 214, "page_hint": null, "section": "Examination of Reactor Vessel Internals", "text": "Arrays were removed after 1087, 4510, 9005, 11,555, and 13,172 equivalent full-power hours."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 226, "line_start": 226, "page_hint": null, "section": "Examination of Fuel Piping", "text": "The MSRE operated for 13,172 equivalent full-power hours with a temperature difference of $40^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ between the fuel entering and leaving the heat exchanger."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 226, "line_start": 226, "page_hint": null, "section": "Examination of Fuel Piping", "text": "Short sections of the 5-inch pipe near the heat exchanger inlet and between the heat exchanger and the reactor vessel should be cut out and examined metallographically for this purpose."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 230, "line_start": 230, "page_hint": null, "section": "Inspection of Fuel Drain Line", "text": "Removal of this section is not practical, but it can be viewed from a distance by removal of heater H-103 and insertion of viewing"}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 236, "line_start": 236, "page_hint": null, "section": "Examination of Charcoal Bed Inlet", "text": "During the initial escalation of the MSRE power in 1966, plugging occurred at several points in the fuel offgas system, including the inlets of the charcoal beds."}
{"claim_type": "table-reference", "line_end": 236, "line_start": 236, "page_hint": null, "section": "Examination of Charcoal Bed Inlet", "text": "There was concern over possible reduction of the adsorptive capacity of the charcoal by the oil residues but no change was detectable from the few thermocouples spaced at 80-ft intervals in the bed."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 244, "line_start": 244, "page_hint": null, "section": "Examination of Thermocouple Wells in Coolant Piping", "text": "Because of the desire to eliminate, insofar as possible, conceivable sources of trouble, the MSRE design included only 2 thermocouple wells in salt piping: one each at the inlet and outlet of the radiator."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 250, "line_start": 250, "page_hint": null, "section": "Examination of Thermocouple Wells in Coolant Piping", "text": "The latter indicated up to 10 percent lower power than the heat balance."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 254, "line_start": 254, "page_hint": null, "section": "Examination of Thermocouple Wells in Coolant Piping", "text": "Except for the small amount of oil leakage (about 2 - 5 cc/day) into the pump bowls, there was no problem with either the coolant-salt or fuel-salt pump in the MSRE."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 254, "line_start": 254, "page_hint": null, "section": "Examination of Thermocouple Wells in Coolant Piping", "text": "The fuel and coolant rotary elements are essentially the same, but the coolant pump operated considerably longer, pumping salt for 26,076 hr compared to 21,788 hr for the fuel pump."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 262, "line_start": 262, "page_hint": null, "section": "Examination of Thermocouple Wells in Coolant Piping", "text": "The Inconel-canned $\\mathrm{Al}_{2}\\mathrm{O}_{3} - \\mathrm{GdO}_{3}$ ceramic poison elements should be checked for dimensional changes and the flexible metal hose and rod should be closely inspected."}
{"claim_type": "salt-chemistry", "line_end": 274, "line_start": 274, "page_hint": null, "section": "Recovery of MSRE Coolant Salt", "text": "The coolant salt, $2610\\mathrm{kg}$ of $\\mathrm{LiF - BeF_2}$ (66 - 34 mole percent), should be melted and removed when required for this purpose."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 282, "line_start": 282, "page_hint": null, "section": "Securing the Plant", "text": "There is currently no demand for the fissile material in the MSRE fuel salt (37 kg U, $84\\%$ $^{233}\\mathrm{U}$ )."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 282, "line_start": 282, "page_hint": null, "section": "Securing the Plant", "text": "Because of the extremely high $^{232}\\mathrm{U}$ content (220 ppm) and consequent radiation problems, it is doubtful that the uranium will ever be worth the cost of recovery from the salt."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 298, "line_start": 298, "page_hint": null, "section": "JOB DESCRIPTIONS", "text": "The letters in each job identification refer to the principal location of the work (RC = reactor cell; DC = drain cell; CC = coolant cell; HC = hot cell at X-10; O = at reactor site outside of cells; L = laboratory)."}
{"claim_type": "table-reference", "line_end": 298, "line_start": 298, "page_hint": null, "section": "JOB DESCRIPTIONS", "text": "The numbers in the job identification refer to the sequence in which the work will probably be done (see Table 2)."}
{"claim_type": "table-reference", "line_end": 298, "line_start": 298, "page_hint": null, "section": "JOB DESCRIPTIONS", "text": "The order in which the jobs are discussed, however, is that in which they are listed in Table 1."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 342, "line_start": 342, "page_hint": null, "section": "Inspect Sampler Cage and Baffle (Job HC-4)", "text": "(There would seem to be no way for the pressure differential to exceed 5 psi or the temperature to exceed $200^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ .)"}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 398, "line_start": 398, "page_hint": null, "section": "Inspect Sampler Cage and Baffle (Job HC-4)", "text": "Use an 18-in.-dia cutting wheel on a mast-mounted tool to cut out 12-in. sections of 5-in. pipe."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 398, "line_start": 398, "page_hint": null, "section": "Inspect Sampler Cage and Baffle (Job HC-4)", "text": "One section will be from Line 101 between the pump discharge and freeze flange 101; the other from the horizontal run of line 102 between the heat exchanger exit and freeze flange 102."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 436, "line_start": 436, "page_hint": null, "section": "Inspect Sampler Cage and Baffle (Job HC-4)", "text": "General Procedure - Cut out a 6-inch section of $3/4$ -inch tube near inlet end of tube bundle and one near outlet end."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 448, "line_start": 448, "page_hint": null, "section": "Inspect Sampler Cage and Baffle (Job HC-4)", "text": "General Procedure - Observing beryllium precautions, cut out a 6-in. section of 5-inch coolant piping containing radiator inlet thermocouple well."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 500, "line_start": 500, "page_hint": null, "section": "Inspect Sampler Cage and Baffle (Job HC-4)", "text": "Purpose - To determine if unbolting system is still operable after over 4 years' exposure."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 512, "line_start": 512, "page_hint": null, "section": "SCHEDULE", "text": "Some of the non-radioactive work, such as that on the coolant system, may begin before July 1, 1970 if funds are available."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 512, "line_start": 512, "page_hint": null, "section": "SCHEDULE", "text": "A target date of July 6 has been set for the beginning of the in-cell work."}
{"claim_type": "table-reference", "line_end": 514, "line_start": 514, "page_hint": null, "section": "SCHEDULE", "text": "Table 2 shows the sequence of in-cell work that now appears most logical, progressing generally from jobs involving less chance of contamination to those likely to involve the most contamination of the cell, tools, and shielding."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 516, "line_start": 516, "page_hint": null, "section": "SCHEDULE", "text": "A goal will be to have virtually all the work of securing the plant finished by October 2, 1970."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 516, "line_start": 516, "page_hint": null, "section": "SCHEDULE", "text": "Hot-cell work and analyses should be completed by December 4, 1970."}
